events.name: Cloud Study Jam

venue.name: Start Innovation Hub
venue.address_1: suite G11 ground floor Ibom e-library

events.description:
• What we'll do
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin?
Join us for our Cloud Study Jam! Together we'll work through three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs, then you will get free access to the next quest so you can finish this series of labs at home to get a Google-hosted badge for your online profile. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Docker, Kubernetes and Scientific Data Processing, which will earn you additional badges.

• What to bring
Bring a laptop (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

• Important to know

events.name: Women Techmakers Uyo IWD 2018 Celebration

venue.name: Start Innovation Hub
venue.address_1: suite G11 ground floor Ibom e-library

events.description:
• What we'll do
International Women's Day (IWD) is marked March 8th every year. The focus of this event ranges from general respect and celebration of women, to a celebration of women's achievements in economic, political and social sectors etc. It is an important period set aside to recognize how women have influenced the various sectors of society. Women Techmakers Uyo (WTM) will celebrate the International Women day the Tech way. WTM Uyo encourages all gender to partake in the WTM Uyo IWD celebration. We will have hands on coding Android things and Machine Learning Study Jam, plus interesting talks and fireside chat sessions as we dive into "Building A New Horizon" to enhance the tech ecosystem.

• What to bring
Laptop
Extension socket

• Important to know

events.name: Starting a Career in Tech

venue.name: Start Innovation Hub
venue.address_1: suite G11 ground floor Ibom e-library

events.description: On 28th February, Women Techmakers Uyo will have a meetup aim at bringing together women with a diverse interest in the technological field who have zero knowledge and perhaps not sure of which path to choose. This will be to properly give them a clear picture of what they are about to channel their passion into, give a headway how to get started, and have them choose which path suits their personality. It is true that technology is becoming the ideal of the present age and it is proper to have everyone, irrespective of age and gender, gain their place in it. And so, they will be given a foundational lecture on areas such as; Web Development, Digital Marketing, Android Development, UI/UX Design, Technical Writing, Content Development, Project/Product Management and of course, Data Science. The meet up will also feature ladies who have already found their strength, share their success stories to motivate and encourage them.

events.name: Cloud Study Jams

venue.name: Start Innovation Hub
venue.address_1: suite G11 ground floor Ibom e-library

events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.
Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want
